<figcaption class="figcaption">Figure 11.2.2. Pachner moves in dimension 3. In the second picture of the 2-3 move, the polyhedron is cut into 3 tetrahedra, all sharing the red edge; thus, any horizontal cross-section looks like the RHS of the 1-3 move in dimension 2. In the 1-4 move, the figure on the right is a tetrahedron cut into 4 tetrahedra, all sharing the center (red) vertex.</figcaption>